customKernelsCategoryName.title: Define the new name for Kernels Section
customKernelsCategoryName.description: Make sure 'Kernels' is defined within categories property. Kernels section includes all the kernels as a default, just replacing the kernel section name.

maxUsageAge.title: Maximal age of the most recent use of a card (in days)
maxUsageAge.description: If the latest use of a card is higher than maxUsageAge, the card will be considered as never used before.

nRecentCards.title: Number of recent cards to display

persistentMostUsedSection.title: To keep Most Used section in Launcher

Featured AI Developer Tools.title: Featured AI Developer Tools Section
Featured AI Developer Tools.description: Items for Featured AI Developer Tools Section

args.title: Neural Network Compression Framework
args.description: Apply advanced algorithms for neural networks inference optimization with minimal accuracy drop using this framework.

args.title: Noise Suppression
args.description: Not Exist, Use a pretrained deep-learning model (noise-suppression-poconetlike-0001) that inputs a noise-induced audio file, and then generates a noise-suppressed audio file.

args.title: Time Series Forecasting
args.description: Not exist, Use a pretrained deep-learning model (time-series-forecasting-electricity-0001) to forecast the time series data from an open-sourced dataset: Electricity.

args.title: Tiny YOLO* V4
args.description: Perform object detection using this pretrained deep-learning model. It inputs a video file and generates an output video that predicts objects and draws a bounding box around them.

args.title: Tiny Yolo V3 Object Detection
args.description: Convert a pretrained Tiny YOLO* V3 model on Darknet to TensorFlow*. Then run accelerated inference for object detection.

args.title: Store Traffic Monitor
args.description: Detect and infer objects with input feeds. Monitor customers and track inventory with a pretrained neural network.

args.title: Store Aisle Monitor
args.description: To detect people in a retail setting, run inference on a pretrained model from the Intel® Distribution of OpenVINO™ toolkit.

args.title: Seismic Interpretation
args.description: An automated seismic interpretation using a convolutional neural network model identifies salt bodies in the Earth's crust.

args.title: Accelerated Object Detection
args.description: Accelerate object detection by using asynchronous inferencing and distributing workloads to multiple types of processing units.

args.title: Machine Translation
args.description: Translate text from English to German and Russian using nonautoregressive transformer models.

args.title: Intruder Detection
args.description: Perform object detection on an input video feed for an application that gives an alert when someone enters a restricted area.

args.title: Frictionless Retail
args.description: Evaluate a typical video analytics pipeline to identify customers as they shop for groceries and automatically bill them.

args.title: Weld Porosity
args.description: Detect arc-welding porosity defects in real time with an end-to-end solution that integrates hardware and software.

args.title: Restricted Zone Notifier
args.description: Create a smart video solution to detect people within a video frame and determine whether they have entered a restricted zone.

args.title: Pneumonia Detection
args.description: Classify the probability of pneumonia in X-Ray images using a pretrained neural network and the Intel® Distribution of OpenVINO™ toolkit.

args.title: People Counter System
args.description: Deploy an IoT solution using a model from the Intel® Distribution of OpenVINO™ toolkit to detect and count people in each frame of a video feed.

args.title: Brain Tumor Segmentation
args.description: Convert and optimize a model based on U-Net for brain tumor segmentation to maximize inference performance on Intel® architecture.

args.title: Biomedical Text Mining
args.description: Perform biomedical question answering using a pretrained BioBERT model and the BioASQ dataset for high-performance inferencing on Intel® hardware.

args.title: American Sign Language (ASL) Gesture Recognition
args.description: Combine person detection and gesture recognition models to identify American Sign Language gestures from a video and attach a text translation.

args.title: OpenVINO™ Integration with TensorFlow* Object Detection
args.description: Find out how to use the native TensorFlow* models with the OpenVINO™ toolkit using an object detection sample application.

args.title: OpenVINO™ Integration with TensorFlow* Classification
args.description: Learn how to use the native TensorFlow* models with the OpenVINO™ toolkit using a classification sample application.

args.title: Mask R-CNN Instance Segmentation
args.description: This sample detects certain objects in an image, draws a bounding box around them, and masks them at the pixel level.

args.title: Shopper Gaze Monitor
args.description: Build a solution to analyze customer expressions and reactions to product advertising positioned on retail shelves.

args.title: Classification
args.description: Classify and report the probability of objects from image and video input with a SqueezeNet 1.1 model and the Intel® Distribution of OpenVINO™ toolkit.

args.title: Benchmark App
args.description: Learn how to use the Intel® DevCloud benchmarking tool to evaluate the performance of your model's synchronous and asynchronous inference.

args.title: Style Transfer
args.description: Restyle images and video frames using a pretrained network and the Intel® Distribution of OpenVINO™ toolkit.

args.title: Post-Training Optimization Tool
args.description: Automate the model transformation process without changing model structure using the Post-Training Optimization Tool.

args.title: OpenCV Tutorial
args.description: Learn about the most common use cases of OpenCV for general image manipulation and the Intel® Distribution of OpenVINO™ toolkit.

args.title: Migrate to DevCloud
args.description: Migrate your IoT application from Intel® DevCloud to your local edge device.

args.title: Migrate to Edge
args.description: Migrate your IoT application from your local edge device to run on a bare metal node.

args.title: OpenVINO™ Integration with TensorFlow*
args.description: Use just two lines of code to rapidly integrate a TensorFlow* model with an image classification application using the Intel® Distribution of OpenVINO™ toolkit.

args.title: Safety Gear Detection
args.description: Detect people and their safety gear from video input that uses an optimized, pretrained MobileNet* single-shot detector (SSD) neural network.
